  "issue_title": "TAO receive address not SS58-checksum-validated \u2014 user typo sends funds irrecoverably",
  "issue_body": "**Severity:** S0 (money-at-risk, user-error amplification)\n\n**Location:** [allways/chain_providers/subtensor.py:276-283](allways/chain_providers/subtensor.py#L276-L283), gated by [allways/cli/swap_commands/swap.py:751](allways/cli/swap_commands/swap.py#L751)\n\n### Bug\n`SubtensorProvider.is_valid_address` only checks 48-char length and Base58 charset via regex \u2014 no SS58 checksum. The string `'xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx'` passes. The swap flow gates on `to_provider.is_valid_address(receive_address)`, so a user who mistypes their TAO destination gets past the only validation gate. The miner later sends TAO to that literal address and the funds are unrecoverable.\n\n### Comparison\n- Bitcoin has proper validation via [bitcoin.py:319-330](allways/chain_providers/bitcoin.py#L319-L330) (bech32 / base58check decode).\n- The correct SS58 pattern already exists at [helpers.py:117-130](allways/cli/swap_commands/helpers.py#L117-L130) wrapping `scalecodec.ss58_decode` \u2014 but it's only used in admin commands.\n\n### Fix\nReplace the regex body of `SubtensorProvider.is_valid_address` with `scalecodec.ss58_decode(address)` wrapped in try/except. Zero behavior change for legitimate addresses; catches all typos.\n\nThe same gap exists for `user_from_address` at [swap.py:757-766](allways/cli/swap_commands/swap.py#L757-L766) but the validator's sender-mismatch check catches that one on-chain.\n\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-20T23:02:29.000Z",
